#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:943
msgid "``spack test list``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:945
msgid ""
"Packages available for install testing can be found using the ``spack test "
"list`` command. The command outputs all installed packages that have defined "
"stand-alone test methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:948
msgid ""
"Alternatively you can use the ``--all`` option to get a list of all packages "
"that have stand-alone test methods even if the packages are not installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:950
msgid "For more information, refer to :ref:`spack-test-list`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:955
msgid "``spack test run``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:957
msgid ""
"Install tests can be run for one or more installed packages using the "
"``spack test run`` command. A ``test suite`` is created for all of the "
"provided specs. The command accepts the same arguments provided to ``spack "
"install`` (see :ref:`sec-specs`). If no specs are provided the command tests "
"all specs in the active environment or all specs installed in the Spack "
"instance if no environment is active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:962
msgid ""
"Test suites can be named using the ``--alias`` option. Unaliased test suites "
"use the content hash of their specs as their name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:965
msgid "Some of the more commonly used debugging options are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:967
msgid "``--fail-fast`` stops testing each package after the first failure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:968
msgid "``--fail-first`` stops testing packages after the first failure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:970
msgid ""
"Test output is written to a text log file by default, though ``junit`` and "
"``cdash`` are outputs available through the ``--log-format`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:972
msgid "For more information, refer to :ref:`spack-test-run`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:978
msgid "``spack test results``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:980
msgid ""
"The ``spack test results`` command shows results for all completed test "
"suites by default. The alias or content hash can be provided to limit "
"reporting to the corresponding test suite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:983
msgid ""
"The ``--logs`` option includes the output generated by the associated "
"test(s) to facilitate debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:985
msgid ""
"The ``--failed`` option limits results shown to that of the failed tests, if "
"any, of matching packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:987
msgid "For more information, refer to :ref:`spack-test-results`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:992
msgid "``spack test find``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:994
msgid ""
"The ``spack test find`` command lists the aliases or content hashes of all "
"test suites whose results are available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:996
msgid "For more information, refer to :ref:`spack-test-find`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:1001
msgid "``spack test remove``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:1003
msgid ""
"The ``spack test remove`` command removes test suites to declutter the test "
"stage directory. You are prompted to confirm the removal of each test suite "
"**unless** you use the ``--yes-to-all`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../packaging_guide_testing.rst:1006
msgid "For more information, refer to :ref:`spack-test-remove`."
msgstr ""
